Pound rides Brexit rollercoaster on D-Day

2016-06-23

Sterling is slipping back in mid-afternoon trading, paring back some of its storming gains which had sent it to as high as $1.4946 – its highest levels seen all year.

Sterling is still 0.6 per cent up on the day but has fallen to as low as $1.479 against the greenback at around 3pm (BST). UK polls close at 10pm with indicators of results due around breakfast time on Friday morning.

